data.name: dialogCaptionBar1.Description
data.value: The selected texture(s) are split into smaller texture tiles, saved to physical files and applied to the respective terrain sector. This feature is useful for terrains with unique texturing from a large database (e.g. using satellite photos)

data.name: textBox1.Text
data.value:
Please select large texture files that should be split into smaller tile textures. Since the created tile textures are copied into the terrain's folder, a source texture outside the project file can be selected.
The dimension of the large texture is constrained in the following way: The edge size divided by the number of sectors must be a power of two, so per-sector textures end up as power-of-two sized textures. If the 'Add filering border' option is enabled, then each tile must be a power-of-two minus 2.
Example: If the terrain consists of 10x10 sectors, then 2560x2560 is a valid source size and per sector textures are equally split into 256x256 textures each. With filter border, 2540x2540 is the valid size in this sample since 254+2 is a power of two.
